# Claude Code Router Setup Instructions
## OpenRouter + Perplexity Configuration

This guide will help you set up Claude Code Router with OpenRouter and Perplexity API.

---

## Prerequisites

1. **OpenRouter Account**: Sign up at https://openrouter.ai/
   - Get your API key from https://openrouter.ai/keys
   - Add credits to your account (pay-as-you-go)

2. **Perplexity Account**: Sign up at https://www.perplexity.ai/
   - Get your API key from https://www.perplexity.ai/settings/api
   - Purchase API credits

---

## Installation Steps

### Step 1: Install Claude Code Router

```bash
npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code
npm install -g @musistudio/claude-code-router
```

### Step 2: Set Up Environment Variables

Add these to your shell configuration file (`~/.zshrc`, `~/.bashrc`, or `~/.bash_profile`):

```bash
export OPENROUTER_API_KEY="sk-or-v1-YOUR-KEY-HERE"
export PERPLEXITY_API_KEY="pplx-YOUR-KEY-HERE"
```

Then reload your shell:
```bash
source ~/.zshrc  # or source ~/.bashrc
```

**Verify your environment variables:**
```bash
echo $OPENROUTER_API_KEY
echo $PERPLEXITY_API_KEY
```

### Step 3: Copy Configuration File

Copy the provided `claude-code-router-config.json` to the router's config directory:

```bash
# Create the directory if it doesn't exist
mkdir -p ~/.claude-code-router

# Copy the config file
cp claude-code-router-config.json ~/.claude-code-router/config.json
```

### Step 4: Start Using Claude Code Router

```bash
ccr code
```

